content.description: Sit start low, matched on a flake. Work your way up the left side of the mini cave. Crux is throwing out left to a good ledge. Easy mantle.
content.location: Just left of the start of Infomercal

content.description: Stand start on fairly positive crimps. Follow the flake like crimps all the way to a so-so mantle.
content.location: The route is to the right of the giant undercling that you will see when approaching the boulder from the road. It's the flatest part of the rock. To get down it's an easy downclimb on the opposite side of the boulder to another smaller boulder.

content.description: Start on the underclings under low roof, slap up right (crux for short kids). Fall in left to large ledge and continue up and over bulge and the double sided arete. Climb up slab to large ledge and up to an easy mantle.
content.location: Located on the front of the thighmaster boulder and a half mile in from the fork in the road. on the right side of the road. The down climb is easiest on the Chicken v2 to the left of the problem.

content.description: Start on the left of the Horn used for Thighmaster. Bump your left hand up to a jug, cross right over to another jug and finish on Chicken.
Stand start in the minicave, moving up using the slopers up to the right and straight above you.
content.location: To the right of Tim's Rash and exact opposite side of Chicken. There is a fair sized boulder just right of the problem.

content.description: Stand start on the horizontal crack and work your way straight up the rock using the sharp jugs and grippy slopers.
content.location: To the left of Thighmaster and just barely to the right of a small boulder on the ground.
